🔹 Secrets & Secure Configurations

👉 What it means --- Handling sensitive data securely in pipelines and infrastructure.

Key Concepts 
    Secrets = passwords, API keys, tokens, certificates
    Never hardcode secrets in code or YAML

Azure Tools:
    Azure Key Vault
    Variable Groups (with secret values)

Best Practices
    Use Key Vault integration in pipelines
    Use managed identities instead of credentials
    Rotate secrets regularly
    Use environment-based configs (Dev/UAT/Prod)

🔹 Infrastructure as Code (IaC)

👉 What it means --- Managing infrastructure using code instead of manual setup.

Tools:
    Terraform (most common)
    Azure Bicep / ARM templates
    CloudFormation (AWS)

Benefits:
    Reusable infrastructure
    Version control
    Consistency across environments
    Faster provisioning

DevOps Flow: Code → Git → Pipeline → Deploy Infra

Example: Create VM, VNet, AKS using Terraform

🔹 Testing & Quality Gates

👉 What it means --- Ensuring code quality before deployment.

Types of Testing:
    Unit Testing
    Integration Testing
    Security Testing (SAST/DAST)

Tools:
    SonarQube (code quality)
    JUnit, NUnit (unit testing)

Quality Gates
    Code coverage threshold
    No critical vulnerabilities
    Build must pass

Pipeline Flow --- Code → Build → Test → Quality Gate → Deploy

🔹 DevSecOps – Security Integration

👉 What it means --- Integrating security into every stage of DevOps.

“Shift Left Security” --- Security starts early (not only at production)

Tools:
    SAST → SonarQube
    DAST → OWASP ZAP
    Container Scan → Trivy
    Dependency Scan → Mend / Snyk

Pipeline Example --- Code → Scan → Build → Scan → Deploy

Key Practices
    Secure coding
    Vulnerability scanning
    Secrets management
    Compliance checks

🔹 Release Strategies

👉 What it means --- Different ways to deploy applications safely.

Types

1️⃣ Blue-Green Deployment ---Two environments (Blue & Green)
    Switch traffic after testing (Zero downtime)

2️⃣ Canary Deployment
    Release to small % of users (Monitor before full rollout)

3️⃣ Rolling Deployment
    Update servers gradually (No downtime, slower rollout)

4️⃣ Recreate Deployment
    Stop old → start new (Simple but downtime)

🔹 Monitoring & Feedback

👉 What it means --- Tracking system performance and feeding data back to improve.

Tools:
    Prometheus (metrics)
    Grafana (dashboard)
    Azure Monitor
    CloudWatch

What to Monitor
    CPU, Memory
    Application logs
    Errors & failures
    Response time

Feedback Loop --- Monitoring → Alerts → Fix → Improve

Example --- Alert triggers → Jira/Azure Board ticket created
